# Unify Lark Webhook Settings and Improve Visibility

The user is unable to find the Lark test feature. My research shows that the test functionality is present in the [WebhookSettingsModal](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/WebhookSettingsModal.tsx#26-308) (used in [DailyMeetingView](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/DailyMeetingView.tsx#2531-2988)) and on the `/sandbox` page, but the [Home](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/app/page.tsx#46-479) page uses an older, inline webhook settings UI that lacks the "Run Test" button.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component Name] Dashboard / UI

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/app/page.tsx)
- Import [WebhookSettingsModal](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/WebhookSettingsModal.tsx#26-308) from `@/components/dashboard/WebhookSettingsModal`.
- Replace the inline webhook settings overlay with the [WebhookSettingsModal](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/WebhookSettingsModal.tsx#26-308) component.
- Ensure the `SANDBOX TEST` link in the header is easily identifiable (it already is, but maybe adding a "New" badge or making it more prominent).

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `npm run build` to ensure no regressions in routing or component imports.

### Manual Verification
1. Open the application.
2. Click the "Members" button in the header.
3. Verify that the [WebhookSettingsModal](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/WebhookSettingsModal.tsx#26-308) opens and contains the "Run Test" section.
4. Input a test webhook URL and click "Run Test".
5. Verify that the test result is displayed correctly.
6. Navigate to the "Sandbox" tab or click the "SANDBOX TEST" button in the header to ensure the dedicated test page is also accessible.
